<TITLE> Switzerland open Euro 2008 against Czechs </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 LUCERNE, Switzerland, Dec 2 (bdnews24.com/Reuters)- Co-hosts Switzerland will face the Czech Republic in the opening match of the Euro 2008 finals while champions Greece open their defence against Sweden following the draw made on Sunday. Switzerland, who face the Czechs in Basel on June 7, were also paired with Portugal and Turkey in Group A. Greece were placed in Group D along with Sweden, who they meet in Salzburg on June 10, and Spain and Russia. Fellow hosts Austria will meet Croatia in their opening match in Vienna in Group B and also face Germany and Poland. The toughest of the four first round groups will be Group C which brings together world champions Italy, beaten World Cup finalists France, the Netherlands and Romania. France and Italy were in the same qualifying group as were the Dutch and Romanians while France also beat Italy in the final of Euro 2000. The championship ends on June 29 in Vienna
